{"lemma":"غِرارُ","slug":"غِرارُ","root":"غ.ر.ر","root_slug":"غ-ر-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ر-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31591"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%90%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"plural of غِرّ (ḡirr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31591","headword_ar":"غِرَارٌ","root":"gr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paucity of milk"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a camel: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deficiency thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See 3.] It is said in a prov., respecting the hastening a thing before its time,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaqa dir~atuhu giraArahu","text_ar":"سَبَقَ دِرَّتُهُ غِرَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His abundant flow of milk preceded his paucity thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (As:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaqa","text_ar":"سَبَقَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dir~atahu giraAruhu","text_ar":"دِرَّتَهُ غِرَارُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his paucity of milk preceded his abundance thereof;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with an explanation of Z, who says that it is applied to him who does evil before he does good: see Freytag's Arab. Prov. i. 613: and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gir~apN","text_ar":"غِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (So in my copies of the S.) ―         -b2-  Hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paucity"},{"kind":"text","text":"of sleep. (As, A'Obeyd, S.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,] in prayer, (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A deficiency in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an imperfect performance of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bowing of the body, and the prostration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the purification."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And in salutation, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in reply to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~alaAmu Ealayokumo","text_ar":"السَّلَامُ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEalayokumo","text_ar":"وَعَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waEalayokumu Als~alaAmu","text_ar":"وَعَلَيْكُمُ السَّلَامُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN Ealayokumo","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"salaAmN Ealayoka","text_ar":"سَلَامٌ عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) [without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"prefixed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"slAm","text_ar":"سلام"},{"kind":"text","text":": as though it were a deficient form; but it is the form specially sanctioned by the Kur-án]: or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"replying by saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayoka","text_ar":"عَلَيْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealyokumo","text_ar":"عَليْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) This is said in explanation of a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lAa giraAra fiY SalaApK walaA tasoliymK","text_ar":"لاَ غِرَارَ فِى صَلَاةٍ وَلَا تَسْلِيمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no deficiency in prayer, nor in salutation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but accord. to one relation, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA grAr fY SlAp","text_ar":"لا غرار فى صلاة"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wlA tasoliyma","text_ar":"ولا تَسْلِيمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, that the person praying shall not salute nor be saluted: in the former case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tslym","text_ar":"تسليم"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an adjunct to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SlAp","text_ar":"صلاة"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the latter, it is an adjunct to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"grAr","text_ar":"غرار"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There shall be no deficiency nor salutation in prayer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Little"},{"kind":"text","text":"sleep (S, K) &c. (K.) El-Farezdak uses the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawomuhun~a girAarN","text_ar":"نَوْمُهُنَّ غِراَرٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Their sleep is little."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And particularly (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Littleness of consideration;"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"haste."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAnaA EalaY girAarK","text_ar":"اَتَانَا عَلَى غِراَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came to us in haste."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytuhu giraArFA","text_ar":"لَقِيتُهُ غِرَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I met him in haste."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^aqamotu Einodahu A_il~aA giraArFA","text_ar":"مَا اَقَمْتُ عِنْدَهُ اـِلَّا غِرَارًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I remained not at his abode save"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a little while."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labiva giraAra $ahorK","text_ar":"لَبِثَ غِرَارَ شَهْرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tarried the space of a month."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota Alyawoma","text_ar":"لَيْتَ اليَوْمَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraAru $ahori","text_ar":"غِرَارُ شَهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that the day were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the length of a month."},{"kind":"text","text":"(So in some copies of the S, and in the O: in other copies of the S,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labiva Alqawomu","text_ar":"لَبِثَ القَوْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraAra $ahorK","text_ar":"غِرَارَ شَهْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like the phrase immediately preceding].) ―         -b7-  And, accord. to As,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraArN","text_ar":"غِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A way, course, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramayotu valaAvapa A^asohumK EalaY giraArK waAHidK","text_ar":"رَمَيْتُ ثَلَاثَةَ اَسْهُمٍ عَلَى غِرَارٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I shot three arrows"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in one course."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waladato","text_ar":"وَلَدَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnapu valaAvapa baniyna EalaY giraArK","text_ar":"فُلَانَةُ ثَلَاثَةَ بَنِينَ عَلَى غِرَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY giraArK waAHidK","text_ar":"عَلَى غِرَارٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a woman brought forth three sons,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one after another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without any girl among them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaY Alqawomu buyuwtahumo EalaY","text_ar":"بَنَى القَوْمُ بُيُوتَهُمْ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraArK waAHidK","text_ar":"غِرَارٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, reared their tents,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, perhaps,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their houses, in one line,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to one manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) ―         -b8-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"model,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pattern, according to which iron heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arrows"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are fashioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to their being made right."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba niSaAlahu EalaY giraArK waAHidK","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ نِصَالَهُ عَلَى غِرَارٍ وَاحِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fashioned his arrow-heads according to"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one model,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pattern."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b9-  And The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or perhaps the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge of the iron head"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the blade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a spear and of an arrow and of a sword: [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gar~N","text_ar":"غَرٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a sword: (K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlgiraAraAni","text_ar":"الغِرَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the [arrow-head called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEobalap","text_ar":"مِعْبَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHn, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two edges"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sword: [see, again,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraArN","text_ar":"غِرَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything that has a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) and the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agir~apN","text_ar":"اَغِرَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["K","As","S","T","TA","M","AHn","O"]}]}}